::::::::::: {.bg-card .rounded-xl .p-8 .border .border-white/5 .space-y-6} In physics, mass and energy are interchangeable. In economics, *physical goods* and *abstract claims on future goods* are treated as equivalent, when they\'re not.
Economic coherence collapses when the ratio between phantom wealth (claims, derivatives, fiat currency) and physical wealth (land, resources, productive capacity) breaks the binding constraint.
